          com.tdunning.math.stats.TDigest digest
          A histogram structure that will record a sketch of a distribution. The compression argument regulates how accuracy should be traded for size? A value of N here will give quantile errors almost always less than 3/N with considerably smaller errors expected for extreme quantiles. Conversely, you should expect to track about 5 N centroids for this accuracy.

          int[] topologicalOrder
          Indexes of graph vertices, in topological order. The topological order defines the order in which forward pass (and hence also backward pass, which is the opposite to this) is conducted in the network.

          Topological sort and vertex index/name + name/index mapping

        • layers

          Layer[] layers
          A list of layers. Each of these layers is present in a GraphVertex, but are here for easy reference. This array also defines the order in which the getLayer(int) method returns layers.

          int numInputArrays
          The number of input arrays to the network. Many networks only have 1 input; however, a ComputationGraph may have an arbitrary number (>=1) separate input arrays

        • numOutputArrays

          The number of output arrays to the network. Many networks only have 1 output; however, a ComputationGraph may have an arbitrary number (>=1) separate output arrays

    • Class org.deeplearning4j.nn.graph.vertex.BaseGraphVertex extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • graph

          ComputationGraph graph

        • vertexName

          String vertexName

        • vertexIndex

          int vertexIndex
          The index of this vertex

        • inputVertices

          VertexIndices[] inputVertices
          A representation of the vertices that are inputs to this vertex (inputs during forward pass) Specifically, if inputVertices[X].getVertexIndex() = Y, and inputVertices[X].getVertexEdgeNumber() = Z then the Zth output of vertex Y is the Xth input to this vertex

        • outputVertices

          VertexIndices[] outputVertices
          A representation of the vertices that this vertex is connected to (outputs duing forward pass) Specifically, if outputVertices[X].getVertexIndex() = Y, and outputVertices[X].getVertexEdgeNumber() = Z then the output of this vertex (there is only one output) is connected to the Zth input of vertex Y

        • inputs

          INDArray[] inputs

        • epsilon

          INDArray epsilon

          For workspaces with learnable size, this variable defines how many cycles will be spent during learning phase

        • overallocationLimit

          double overallocationLimit
          If OVERALLOCATION policy is set, memory will be overallocated in addition to initialSize of learned size

        • stepsNumber

          int stepsNumber
          This value is used only for circular workspaces

  • Package org.nd4j.parameterserver.distributed.conf

    • Class org.nd4j.parameterserver.distributed.conf.VoidConfiguration extends Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • streamId

          int streamId
          StreamId is used for Aeron configuration

        • unicastControllerPort

          int unicastControllerPort
          This variable defines UDP port that will be used for communication with cluster driver.
          NOTE: Use #setPortSupplier(PortSupplier) to set the port to use - the value of the unicastControllerPort field will automatically be updated to the value set by the PortSupplier provided on the master/controller machine, before communicating to the worker machines. Setting this field directly will NOT control the port that is used.

        • multicastPort

          int multicastPort
          This method specifies UDP port for multicast/broadcast transport

        • numberOfShards

          int numberOfShards
          This method defines number of shards. Reserved for future use.

        • faultToleranceStrategy

          FaultToleranceStrategy faultToleranceStrategy
          Reserved for future use.

        • executionMode

          ExecutionMode executionMode
          Reserved for future use.

        • shardAddresses

          List<E> shardAddresses
          Reserved for future use.

        • backupAddresses

          List<E> backupAddresses
          Reserved for future use.

        • transportType

          TransportType transportType
          This variable defines network transport to be used for comms

        • meshBuildMode

          MeshBuildMode meshBuildMode
          This variable defines how cluster nodes are organized

        • networkMask

          String networkMask
          This variable acts as hint for ParameterServer about IP address to be used for comms. Used only if SPARK_PUBLIC_DNS is undefined (i.e. as in YARN environment)

        • multicastNetwork

          String multicastNetwork
          This value is optional, and has effect only for UDP MulticastTransport

        • multicastInterface

          String multicastInterface
          This value is optional, and has effect only for UDP MulticastTransport

        • ttl

          int ttl
          This value is optional, and has effect only for UDP MulticastTransport

        • forcedRole

          NodeRole forcedRole
          This option is for debugging mostly. Do not use it, unless you have to.

        • useHS

          boolean useHS
          Deprecated. 
          This value is optional, and has effect only for UDP MulticastTransport

        • useNS

          boolean useNS
          Deprecated. 
          This value is optional, and has effect only for UDP MulticastTransport

        • retransmitTimeout

          long retransmitTimeout
          This variable defines, how long transport should wait before resending message in case of network issues. Measured in milliseconds.

        • responseTimeframe

          long responseTimeframe
          This variable defines, how long transport should wait for response on specific messages.

        • responseTimeout

          long responseTimeout
          This variable defines, how long transport should wait for answer on specific messages.

        • chunksBufferSize

          long chunksBufferSize
          This variable defines amount of memory used of Default value: 1GB

        • maxChunkSize

          int maxChunkSize
          This variable defines max chunk size for INDArray splits

        • maxFailuresPerNode

          int maxFailuresPerNode
          This variable defines max number of allowed reconnects per node

        • controllerAddress

          String controllerAddress
          This optional variable defines IP address of the box which acts as master for gradients training. Leave it null, and Spark Master node will be used as Master for parameter server as well.

        • portSupplier

          PortSupplier portSupplier
          The port supplier used to provide the networking port to use for communication to/from the driver (UDP via Aeron). This setting can be used to control how ports get assigned (including port setting different ports on different machines).
          See PortSupplier for further details.
          Default: static port (i.e., StaticPortSupplier) with value VoidConfiguration.DEFAULT_AERON_UDP_PORT
